<HEADLINE>
<P>
DRAWING FROM A HAT DECIDES WYOMING RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In a race decided by a Ping-Pong ball, Republican Randall Luthi won a seat in 
the state House on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 A ball bearing Luthi's name was drawn from the battered cowboy hat of Gov. 
Mike Sullivan during a meeting of the state Canvassing Board, settling the race 
Luthi tied with independent Larry Call. 
</P>
<P>
 Each candidate got 1,941 votes in the Nov. 8 election. State law calls for 
such ties to be settled by drawing lots. 
</P>
<P>
 "It is democracy at its best," proclaimed the declared winner. 
</P>
</TEXT>
