<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; MAN ROBS 2ND BANK WITHIN A MONTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIGUEL BUSTILLO FO Suspect in Oxnard bank robbery 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The FBI is searching for a man who on Wednesday robbed his second bank in 
Oxnard within the past month. 
</P>
<P>
 The robber, described as a Latino in his 20s with a light mustache, walked 
into a Bank of America branch on A Street in downtown Oxnard about 9:30 a.m. 
with a brown bag, told the teller that he had a pistol and handed over a note 
demanding money, said FBI Special Agent Larry Dick. 
</P>
<P>
 "He did it in such a way that no one noticed what was happening," Dick said. 
"Only one bank worker was aware that a robbery was taking place."  
</P>
<P>
 FBI agents quickly determined that Wednesday's robber was the same man who 
held up a Bank of America on Saviers Road on Oct. 26, because the descriptions 
given by witnesses, the words used to ask for money and the notes all matched, 
Dick said. 
</P>
<P>
 Furthermore, surveillance cameras captured several clear shots of the man 
during each holdup. 
</P>
<P>
 Dick declined to say how much money the man had robbed or what he said to the 
tellers when asking for money. 
</P>
<P>
 Bank of America officials were not available for comment Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The robbery was the 21st of the year in the county, Dick said. There were 45 
robberies in all of 1993. MIGUEL BUSTILLOFO Suspect in Oxnard bank robbery 
</P>
</TEXT>
