<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: BURBANK; ENTRANTS SOUGHT FOR DECORATING CONTEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM MAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Burbank Civic Pride Committee is seeking entrants for its 12th annual 
Holiday Outdoor Decorating Contest.  
</P>
<P>
 Categories this year include Christmas lights, animated scenes, most creative, 
children's theme, window displays and commercial/business decorations.Residents 
may enter as an entire neighborhood, block or street. 
</P>
<P>
 Entry forms were mailed out with the city's utility bills earlier this month. 
Forms are available in the City Hall lobby and at all city libraries and 
recreation centers, or entries may be submitted on a plain sheet of paper 
including name, address, phone number and category of competition.  
</P>
<P>
 Forms should be mailed to: Civic Pride, Public Information Office, Burbank 
Central Library, 110 N. Glenoaks Blvd., Burbank 91502. 
</P>
<P>
 The displays will be judged by the 10-member Burbank Civic Pride Committee, 
which is appointed annually by the City Council. The committee's goal is to 
promote pride and generate interest in the city by organizing activities and 
recognizing those who work to beautify their communities. 
</P>
<P>
 Cinda Cates, the city's public information specialist, said the annual contest 
typically draws about 60 entries. Winners in each category receive honorary 
plaques at the Dec. 20 City Council meeting, which is broadcast on government 
access cable TV Channel 21 at 7 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Cates said the children's theme category became part of the contest last year. 
It is open to displays designed and created by children 15 years old and 
younger.  
</P>
<P>
 The animation category was added about three years ago.  
</P>
<P>
 For more information, contact the city of Burbank public information office at 
(818) 953-8727. TIM MAY 
</P>
</TEXT>
