<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: LA MIRADA; COUNTY MAY DONATE PARKLAND FOR GYM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN CANALIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The county has tentatively agreed to donate one acre of La Mirada Regional 
Park to the city to build a $2-million gymnasium. 
</P>
<P>
 County parks and recreation officials have issued a letter saying they will 
deed the land to La Mirada if the city provides office space in the gym for a 
county recreation staff member and agrees to care for landscaping near the 
facility. 
</P>
<P>
 The provisions also require the city to maintain a parking lot next to the gym 
site off Alicante Road and to expand it if the gym creates a parking shortage. 
Los Angeles County supervisors could approve the land transfer within a few 
weeks, said Henry Roman, the county's assistant parks and recreation director. 
</P>
<P>
 The county has given away about 11 parkland sites to cities in the last two 
years. JOHN CANALIS 
</P>
