<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: PICO RIVERA; EX-CANDIDATE GUILTY OF VIOLATING COURT ORDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN D. WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Superior Court jury has convicted a former City Council candidate of 
violating a court order to stay away from his former wife. 
</P>
<P>
 David W. Armenta, 44, was placed on probation for a year by Judge John A. 
Torribio and was ordered to avoid contacting his former wife, Robin Cordova, 
41. 
</P>
<P>
 Armenta, who ran unsuccessfully for council earlier this year, was acquitted 
of four other charges, including stalking and threatening Cordova and hitting a 
friend of hers, George Karavolos, 19, in the face. 
</P>
<P>
 Armenta and Cordova were divorced last year after 16 years of marriage. JOHN 
D. WAGNER 
