<P>
 United Shuttle Offers Special Thanksgiving Fares: If you thought Thanksgiving 
turkey prices were a bargain, consider the air fare deal just announced by 
United Airlines' new Shuttle: $9.97 to fly between Southern California and the 
Bay Area.The promotional fare, designed to increase awareness of the new 
service and an electronic ticketing system, is available on a limited number of 
seats on 300 flights, the airline said. It is only good from noon on 
Thanksgiving Day until noon Saturday. By Wednesday afternoon, about 3,000 of 
the 5,600 available seats were already taken, according to United spokesman Joe 
Hopkins. All the revenue goes to charity, he said. 
