<TEXT>
<P>
 EU Says Airlines May Get Special Aid: The European Commission, the executive 
body of the European Union, said carriers that have received state aid can get 
more under special circumstances, a decision that could help Spain's 
cash-strapped national airline, Iberia, but threaten successful airlines such 
as British Airways and KLM Royal Dutch Airlines. British Airways and KLM, vocal 
opponents of aid, and other carriers have sued to overturn the $3.2 billion in 
state aid recently granted to Air France. If the suit, brought in the European 
Court of Justice, is successful, the commission could be forced to reconsider 
its position. 
</P>
