<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: INVESTOR'S LAWSUIT SEEKS TO BLOCK AMERIQUEST SALE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AmeriQuest Technologies Inc. said Wednesday that it has been sued by an 
investor seeking to block a proposed sale of the company to a German 
corporation. 
</P>
<P>
 The suit, which seeks class-action status, alleges that the board of 
AmeriQuest breached its fiduciary duty when it agreed Monday to sell a majority 
stake to Computer 2000 AG, a German hardware and software distributor. 
</P>
<P>
 The acquisition, subject to approval of both companies' shareholders, would 
provide the first foothold for a European distributor in the U.S. microcomputer 
market, Computer 2000 said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The lawsuit was filed in Delaware by shareholder Erica Hartman. Her stake in 
AmeriQuest was not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
 AmeriQuest, based in Irvine, distributes microcomputer systems, peripherals 
and software to computer resellers, systems integrators and retailers. Company 
officials could not be reached for comment Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
