<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUPLE DIES IN MURDER-SUICIDE; CRIME: DURING AN ARGUMENT, DAVID DAVTYAN SHOOTS 
HIS WIFE, VARDUSH DAVTYAN, THEN COMMITS SUICIDE. SHE DIES AN HOUR LATER. HIS 
MOTHER HEARD THE SHOTS. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERROL A. COCKFIELD JR. and JEANNETTE REGALADO, TIMES STAFF WRITERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A husband fatally shot his wife during a quarrel in the bedroom of their 
apartment Wednesday, then committed suicide, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 David Davtyan 36, died instantly from the single gunshot to the head at the 
apartment in the 500 block of East Windsor Road.His wife, Vardush Davtyan, 37, 
died of a head wound an hour later at Glendale Memorial Hospital, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 David's mother, Perchuhy Davtyan, 63, said she was in another room of the 
apartment when she heard the two shots at about 2 p.m. She "knew they were 
engaged in serious discussion regarding their marital problems," said Lt. 
Raymond Edey of the Glendale Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
 They were both shot with a .380-caliber semiautomatic pistol registered to 
David Davtyan that he bought in June, said Edey. 
</P>
<P>
 Late Wednesday, grieving relatives and friends gathered in a neighboring 
apartment unit, some in tears, and said they were shocked at the 
murder-suicide. 
</P>
<P>
 Rima Ter-Galstanyan, 18, said she heard the dead man's mother scream, ran over 
to their apartment and called police. "She heard the shots but didn't know what 
they were," Ter-Galstanyan said. 
</P>
<P>
 The couple's three children, ages 10 to 14, were at school at the time of the 
shootings and are staying with a nearby relative, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 David's father, Petros Davtyan, 84, sat quietly at the dinner table with his 
head down but would not speak. 
</P>
<P>
 Jiny Hwang, 17, lives with her parents in the apartment adjacent to the 
Davtyans. She said the argument before the shootings sounded like "someone was 
smashing furniture." 
</P>
<P>
 "We knew they had some kind of problem because they fought a lot," said Jiny, 
a friend of the couple's oldest child. "We could hear it through the walls." 
</P>
