STUDENT FILM, VIDEO PROGRAMS SCHEDULED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The American Cinematheque, in collaboration with the University Film and Video 
Assn., presents the best of the second annual UFVA Student Film & Video 
Festival in two different 92-minute programs at 7 p.m. and 9 p.m. Saturday in 
the Chaplin Theater, Raleigh Studios, 5300 Melrose Ave. (between Bronson and 
Van Ness avenues). 
</P>
