</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Julie Adams, the only returning starter from Cypress' 26-4 girls' basketball 
team, decided Wednesday to leave the program to concentrate on softball. 
</P>
<P>
 Adams' decision came after she received confirmation that she is one of 39 
national finalists for the U.S. Junior World team that will conduct tryouts 
Jan. 3-8 at Cal State Fullerton.There, the group will be pared to 17. 
</P>
<P>
 "I've been hurt in basketball before, and if I get hurt at all, there's no 
chance for me," said Adams, a shortstop who will attend UCLA on a softball 
scholarship. 
</P>
<P>
 "The ultimate goal is to be in the Olympics, and this is one step closer. I 
would never forgive myself if, a week before the tryouts, I broke my ankle in a 
basketball game. 
</P>
<P>
 "I look at this as a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity and I want to give it my 
best shot and be as ready as I can be." 
</P>
<P>
 Adams averaged 17.3 points, 13.5 rebounds and shot 56% from the field last 
year. MARTIN HENDERSON 
