<BYLINE>
<P>
By JIM HODGES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chris Andersen will have his mind on the USC-UCLA game Saturday, but he will 
be listening to the scores on the public address system at the Rose Bowl. Of 
particular interest: Alabama vs. Auburn. 
</P>
<P>
 Andersen called KLOS radio Tuesday and bet Mark Thompson of the "Mark and 
Brian Show" that Alabama, with former UCLA assistant Homer Smith as its 
offensive coordinator, would beat Auburn. 
</P>
<P>
 The stakes: If Alabama wins, Thompson will sing the Crimson Tide's fight song 
to Andersen. If Auburn wins, Andersen, UCLA's long snapper, has to sing USC's 
fight song. Actually, the bet was $20, made over the air, but then Andersen got 
a call from the station. "Somebody told them it was against NCAA rules for me 
to bet on a college game," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Though Thompson might have to look up Alabama's fight song, Andersen will have 
no trouble remembering USC's "Fight On." His father, Foster, played and coached 
at UCLA and was a USC assistant for 14 years, under John McKay and John 
Robinson. 
</P>
<P>
