<P>
WARRIORS SIGN WEBBER; TRADE POSSIBILITY LOOMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chris Webber re-signed Wednesday night with the Golden State Warriors after a 
bitter contract dispute, but that did little to quell speculation he might not 
remain with the team. 
</P>
<P>
 The Warriors, who did not release terms of the agreement, said Webber was 
expected to rejoin the team Friday or Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The signing came at the end of a holdout that led Coach Don Nelson to say he 
would quit if such a move would facilitate signing Webber, who has said he was 
unhappy playing for Nelson last season. 
</P>
<P>
 Webber was angered at Nelson for making such a suggestion, and meanwhile his 
agents said they were investigating possible trades with four teams, including 
the Clippers. 
</P>
<P>
 By signing Webber, the Warriors now would be able to trade him. They could not 
have traded Webber, or even negotiated with other teams about a trade, while he 
remained an unsigned restricted free agent. 
</P>
<P>
 "We continue with the speculation," agent Bill Strickland said in response to 
a question about whether Webber would soon be traded. "He's under contract with 
the Warriors, and that's all I can say at this time. He's happy to have signed 
his contract, and hopefully we can move beyond what has been a press spectacle 
out there." 
</P>
<P>
 Webber has missed the team's first six games. 
</P>
