leading scorer last season, averaging 7.8 points. This year, she has improved 
her ability to drive to the basket. The Highlanders, aside from Lien, are 
short, which could hurt in a league filled with talented post players. "Height 
will be a problem," Koehler said. "We have to run, press and rattle the other 
team a little bit. We're going to go after them and create activity." SCHEDULE 
