<P>
 Kameoka, who averaged 14 points last season and was a first-team all-league 
selection, returns for her fourth year on varsity. "She's really competitive," 
Del Crognale said. "She's a really good shooter, but her hindrance is that 
she's only 5 feet 3." And therein lies the Lancers' biggest problem: Del 
Crognale says he probably won't have any starters taller than 5-9. "This is my 
third year coaching here, and the first year, I thought we were short. Since 
then, we've gotten shorter every year. That's a scary thought." Gonzales and 
Kaminiski, who was the junior varsity's most valuable player, should provide 
rebounding and defensive help. "(Gonzales) is the enforcer," Del Crognale said. 
He said he doesn't expect much scoring from either player. Kameoka and 
Kaneshiro will start in the backcourt, but Chen might play some at point guard, 
depending on how soon she adapts to varsity play. The Lancers must make up for 
their lack of height with tenacity, Del Crognale said. "We've got some 
aggressive girls and some good shooters, it's just a matter of getting some 
rebounds." SCHEDULE 
