and Darke to press and trap frequently, to try to take advantage of a new rule 
forbidding teams from re-entering the backcourt. But the key to this team is 
Nadia Hoerner. She led the Freeway League in scoring with 21 points per game. 
"She can be a dominating player if she does in games what she does in 
practice," he said. "You hate to depend on one player so much, but I'd be a 
fool not to take advantage of her ability." Perez is also excited about 
Cooper's offensive skills. "She's an excellent shooter, a good three-point 
shooter, a good defender and has good court sense." She will play both guard 
positions. Clark, MacShane and Shannon Hoerner will provide front-court depth. 
