</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Latino professionals were honored by United Way of Orange County this week for 
their community contributions through business and volunteer efforts. 
</P>
<P>
 All six honorees had been named in the October issue of Hispanic Business 
Magazine as being among the "100 Influentials" nationwide. 
</P>
<P>
 They were: 
</P>
<P>
 * Mary Alice Acevedo, the Republican challenger in this month's 50th 
Congressional District race (won by incumbent Bob Filner of San Diego); 
</P>
<P>
