<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; MAN FOUND FATALLY STABBED IN PARKING LOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TINA NGUYEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 27-year-old man was found stabbed to death early Wednesday morning in a 
restaurant parking lot in Little Saigon, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Garden Grove resident was attacked in a strip mall lot in the 10500 block 
of Bolsa Avenue and suffered multiple stab wounds.The attack may have involved 
more than one assailant, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police declined to release the victim's name Wednesday, saying they had not 
yet contacted his family. 
</P>
<P>
 A passerby called police sometime after 11 p.m. Tuesday night to report a 
wounded man in the parking lot. When police arrived, they found the dead man 
and blood on his car and nearby bushes. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said they do not know why officers didn't arrive at the scene until 
after midnight. 
</P>
<P>
 Police do not believe the victim was robbed because his wallet was found in 
his pocket. 
</P>
<P>
 At the intersection of Bolsa and Ward, a generally peaceful corner where the 
strip mall is located, most business owners were unaware of the killing 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 "The worst violence I ever heard of was a car break-in and the stereo was 
stolen a few months back," said a doctor's assistant, whose office in the strip 
mall. "But this is frightening news. It makes me think about how we should 
schedule our work hours." 
</P>
<P>
 Vincent Truong, manager of the Kim Su Restaurant, was alarmed by the killing 
but said he does not plan to increase security at his restaurant, located not 
far from where the body was found. Truong currently employs two security 
guards. 
</P>
<P>
 "Things like this usually don't happen. This is probably an isolated 
incident," Truong said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police have no suspects in the attack and are continuing their investigation. 
TINA NGUYEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
